In order to preview the slide to ensure that all information and formats are displayed correctly, we need to start the slide show function to show the current slide. In LibreOffice Impress, this can usually be done by clicking the slide show icon on the toolbar, or by pressing the keyboard shortcut. Based on screenshots, the slide show is located near the top of the window.
Here is the JSON format for executing actions:```json
[
    {"action_type": "MouseAction", "mouse_action_type": "click", "mouse_button": "left", "mouse_position": {"width": 747, "height": 67}}
]
```
